commentPreTextItems.html: Mohammad Yousuf on to bowl. He has bowled just one ball in ODIs ...

commentTextItems.html: slow and loopy, driven to cover where Inzamam holds the catch. Huge grins all round, and Yousuf has not smiled more when he's scored hundreds. Even Simon Taufel can't help grinning

commentPostTextItems.html: Pakistan have won the match by 93 runs (D/L) but both sides are eliminated and Ireland will join West Indies in the Super Eights. Many thanks for staying with us throughout the long rain delay ... from me, Martin Williamson, and a coughing and wheezing Will Luke, it's goodnight until tomorrow.

Inzamam leads the side off for the final time, acknowledges the applause and shakes hands with all the Zimbabwe side who have come on to meet and congratulate the Pakistan side. The rest of the Pakistan squad are also on the field and he hugs them all in turn as they applaud him.

commentTextItems.html: very wide, he used his full reach and steered that to deep cover

commentPostTextItems.html: and so to Pakistan and Zimbabwe's final over in the tournament
